data.name: Teriyaki Chicken Lettuce Wraps
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy teriyaki chicken served in crisp lettuce wraps for a fresh and healthy meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a skillet over medium heat, add the chicken thighs and cook until browned, about 6-7 minutes on each side.
Add the teriyaki sauce to the skillet, and simmer for an additional 5 minutes until the chicken is cooked through and coated in sauce.
Remove the chicken from the skillet and let it rest for a few minutes before dicing it into small pieces.
In a bowl, combine the diced chicken, chopped green onions, diced water chestnuts, and shredded carrots.
To serve, spoon the chicken mixture into the butter lettuce leaves, and sprinkle sesame seeds on top.
